229 (b) Notwithstanding any other laws to the contrary, the
230 funds appropriated to the Department of Education by
231 subsection (a) of this section shall not be expended without
232 prior approval of the State Superintendent of Education.
233 (c)(1) The above appropriation for teacher professional
234 development shall be allocated to the Alabama Department of
Page 10

development shall be allocated to the Alabama Department of
HB236 INTRODUCED
235 Education to be distributed to the Ed Farm Classroom of
236 Tomorrow. These funds will be used by Ed Farm to provide
237 technology tools and professional development services to
238 classroom teachers in an effort to improve instruction and
239 student learning gains. It is the intent of the legislature
240 that in addition to general programmatic costs, Ed Farm may
241 also expend funds for software, hardware, administrative
242 costs, and professional learning services.
243 (2) The State Superintendent shall provide a report of the
244 initiative to the Chair of the House Ways and Means-Education
245 Committee and the Chair of the Senate Committee on Finance and
246 Taxation-Education no later than October 1, 2027.
247 Section 4. (a) Notwithstanding the provisions of
248 Section 29-9-4, Code of Alabama 1975, and in addition to all
249 other appropriations heretofore or hereafter made, there is
250 hereby appropriated a total of $100,000,000 from the Education
251 Trust Fund Advancement and Technology Fund to the Department
252 of Education to provide matching grants to local education
253 agencies for expenses related to developing regional career
254 technology centers throughout the state, including capital
255 outlay and equipment, for the fiscal year ending September 30,
256 2026. Grant proposals shall be submitted by a collaboration of
257 at lease two local education agencies. The State
258 Superintendent of Education shall utilize a sliding scale of
Page 11

Superintendent of Education shall utilize a sliding scale of
HB236 INTRODUCED
259 matching requirements for grant proposals, taking into
260 consideration the financial capacity of the eligible local
261 education agencies to provide matching funds, so long as the
262 required match does not exceed 50 percent of the total cost of
263 the project.
264 (b) The State Superintendent of Education shall notify
265 each local superintendent and finance officer of each local
266 education agency by email regarding the availability and
267 application process of grants to be awarded pursuant to this
268 section, including any required forms. The State
269 Superintendent shall notify all members of the local
270 legislative delegation five days prior to the announcement of
271 any grant made to any entity located in the legislative
272 jurisdiction. The five days prior notice requirement shall be
273 waived in the event of a declared emergency. The Governor
274 shall encourage the Department to disburse the funds provided
275 herein on a nondiscriminatory basis.
276 Section 5. All funds appropriated herein and not
277 expended in the current fiscal year shall not revert but be
278 carried forward for the purpose appropriated.
279 Section 6. This act shall become effective immediately
280 following its passage and approval by the Governor, or its
281 otherwise becoming law.
